oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Henry Sheffield
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Henry Sheffield wearing a Masonic Knights Templar uniform, with a skull and cross on the table beside him.

Henry Sheffield was a Connecticut-born doctor of homeopathic medicine who settled in Nashville. During the Civil War, he was in charge of a ward at the Military Railroad Hospital. He was a Grand Captain General and a Commander in the Nashville Commandery of the Knights Templar.
